Spec: SpecDD Review Skill

Purpose:
  Guide agents in reviewing diffs, branches, pull requests, changed files, or proposed changes against active SpecDD contracts.

Owns:
  ./specdd-review/SKILL.md.ejs
  ./specdd-review/agents/openai.yaml

Must:
  Resolve governing specs for changed files before judging the diff.
  Compare changes against applicable `Must`, `Must not`, `Forbids`, `Scenario`, `Tasks`, and `Done when` entries.
  Check whether verification matches the behavioral risk.
  Lead with concrete findings tied to files, behavior, and violated contracts.
  Order findings by severity.
  Include file and line when available, the violated or risky contract, concrete behavior or regression risk, and the smallest likely fix.
  Include open questions or assumptions after findings.
  Say clearly when there are no findings and mention residual test or spec coverage gaps.

Must not:
  Edit files unless the user explicitly asks for changes.
  Invent violations beyond the active specs.
  Hide underspecified behavior as an implementation defect.
  Treat underspecified behavior as a violation instead of uncertainty.

Depends on:
  ../fragments/bootstrap-resolution.md.ejs
  ../fragments/spec-chain-resolution.md.ejs
